#MEM id=rules source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/dev/skills/design-and-build/vercel-composition-patterns/rules/state-decouple-implementation.md
M|rules|title: Decouple State Management from UI
M|rules|impact: MEDIUM
M|rules|impactDescription: enables swapping state implementations without changing UI
M|rules|tags: composition, state, architecture
M|rules|The provider component should be the only place that knows how state is managed.
M|rules|UI components consume the ctx interface—they don't know if state comes from
M|rules|useState, Zustand, or a server sync.
M|rules|**Incorrect (UI coupled to state implementation):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|function ChannelComposer({ channelId }: { channelId: string }) {
M|rules|// UI component knows about global state implementation
M|rules|const state = useGlobalChannelState(channelId)
M|rules|const { submit, updateInput } = useChannelSync(channelId)
M|rules|return (
M|rules|<Composer.Frame>
M|rules|<Composer.Input
M|rules|value={state.input}
M|rules|onChange={(text) => sync.updateInput(text)}
M|rules|/>
M|rules|<Composer.Submit onPress={() => sync.submit()} />
M|rules|</Composer.Frame>
M|rules|)
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (state management isolated in provider):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|// Provider handles all state management details
M|rules|function ChannelProvider({
M|rules|channelId,
M|rules|children,
M|rules|}: {
M|rules|channelId: string
M|rules|children: React.ReactNode
M|rules|}) {
M|rules|const { state, update, submit } = useGlobalChannel(channelId)
M|rules|const inputRef = useRef(null)
M|rules|return (
M|rules|<Composer.Provider
M|rules|state={state}
M|rules|actions={{ update, submit }}
M|rules|meta={{ inputRef }}
M|rules|>
M|rules|{children}
M|rules|</Composer.Provider>
M|rules|)
M|rules|}
M|rules|// UI component only knows about the ctx interface
M|rules|function ChannelComposer() {
M|rules|return (
M|rules|<Composer.Frame>
M|rules|<Composer.Header />
M|rules|<Composer.Input />
M|rules|<Composer.Footer>
M|rules|<Composer.Submit />
M|rules|</Composer.Footer>
M|rules|</Composer.Frame>
M|rules|)
M|rules|}
M|rules|// Usage
M|rules|function Channel({ channelId }: { channelId: string }) {
M|rules|return (
M|rules|<ChannelProvider channelId={channelId}>
M|rules|<ChannelComposer />
M|rules|</ChannelProvider>
M|rules|)
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Different providers, same UI:**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|// Local state for ephemeral forms
M|rules|function ForwardMessageProvider({ children }) {
M|rules|const [state, setState] = useState(initialState)
M|rules|const forwardMessage = useForwardMessage()
M|rules|return (
M|rules|<Composer.Provider
M|rules|state={state}
M|rules|actions={{ update: setState, submit: forwardMessage }}
M|rules|>
M|rules|{children}
M|rules|</Composer.Provider>
M|rules|)
M|rules|}
M|rules|// Global synced state for channels
M|rules|function ChannelProvider({ channelId, children }) {
M|rules|const { state, update, submit } = useGlobalChannel(channelId)
M|rules|return (
M|rules|<Composer.Provider state={state} actions={{ update, submit }}>
M|rules|{children}
M|rules|</Composer.Provider>
M|rules|)
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|The same `Composer.Input` component works with both providers because it only
M|rules|depends on the ctx interface, not the implementation.